festival.introText:
Good Vibrations Society is an event for old and young to enjoy music and wellness in the beautiful surroundings of the Ashdown forest. An invitation to experience community in all its glory. Join us to celebrate friendship, expression, personality and Nature.

Dance to incredible musicians from around the world; wake up to wild swimming; free yoga and dance workshops; stimulate your mind with daily talks and conversation; play in an evolving playscape; explore the forest with guided walks and take the weight off with a cold beverage in our onsite pub or hearty meal in our seated restaurant.

faqs.question: When is Good Vibrations Society 2023?
faqs.answer: Good Vibrations Society takes place Friday 4th August - Sunday 6th August 2023.

faqs.question: What happens if I bought a ticket and cannot attend?
faqs.answer: Unfortunately we can’t issue you with a refund if you can’t make the event due to work commitments or your mates have dropped out. In these circumstances, we advise passing on your tickets privately to avoid losing out on the money spent. Refunds can only be offered if the event is cancelled or postponed, as agreed upon purchase.

faqs.question: How to get to Good Vibrations Society
faqs.answer: Good Vibrations Society is located Park Manor, Nutley, Uckfield TN22 3HW

faqs.question: What facilities are available inside the campsite?
faqs.answer: There will be plenty of room to enjoy the stunning Ashdown Forest safely. There will be warm showers, drinking water, toilets and an onsite supplies shop courtesy of Harvest Supplies the Ashdown Forest based organic healthfood shop. This will be the perfect environment to enjoy the weekend.

faqs.question: Accessibility information
faqs.answer:
Good Vibrations Society takes place in wild countryside, please bear this in mind as the ground may be poor or unmade.

 

If you have specific requirements please contact accessibility@goodvibrationssociety.com and they will do our best to help you.

faqs.question: Where is Good Vibrations Society?
faqs.answer: Good Vibrations Society is located at Pippingford Park Manor, Nutley, Uckfield TN22 3HW.

faqs.question: Types of tickets
faqs.answer:
Weekend tickets give you access to the site from 12:00 noon on Friday 5th august until 12:00 noon on Monday 8th august. Day tickets give you access to the site from 12:00 noon on the day purchased until 11:00am the following day.

 

All tickets come with camping for the night(s) that come after the day(s) purchased, although you don’t have to camp if you don’t wish!

faqs.question: Parking
faqs.answer: There is parking on site a short walk from the campsite. Parking is priced at £6 per car, regardless of duration.

faqs.question: Can I bring a caravan / camper van?
faqs.answer: Yes! There are dedicated pitches for caravans and campervans. However this must be booked in advance, look for the applicable option on the booking screen. You will also need a normal ticket for each occupant to access the event.

faqs.question: When can I arrive at Good Vibrations Society?
faqs.answer: The wristband exchange will be open 12:00 noon until 8:30pm each day. Please don’t arrive outside of these times.

faqs.question: E-Tickets & Wristband Exchange
faqs.answer: All tickets are delivered as e-tickets via e-mail. On entrance to the festival your ticket will be scanned and a wristband issued. This wristband then acts as your ticket for the remainder of your stay.

faqs.question: Train
faqs.answer:
Victoria to East Grinstead line:

This terminates at East Grinstead and runs every half hour through the day. Journey time from Victoria is 55 minutes.

Taxis from the East Grinstead station take 15 minutes.

 

Bedford to Brighton Line:

Stop at Haywards Heath.

Taxis from Haywards Heath station take 25 minutes.

 

Victoria to Brighton Line:

Stop at Haywards Heath.

Taxis from Haywards Heath station take 25 minutes.

faqs.question: Can I bring my own booze?
faqs.answer:
Day ticket holders are not permitted to bring alcohol onsite.

 

Each weekend ticket holder may bring:

12x cans of beer/lager or cider

OR

12x 250ml cans of pre-mixed spirit and mixer

OR

75cl of spirit in a non-glass container

OR

2.25 litres of wine (which must be decanted into a non-glass container)

faqs.question: Are there any age restrictions at Good Vibrations Society?
faqs.answer:
All ages are welcome into the Good Vibrations Society. Anyone under 18 must be accompanied by an adult 25 or older at all times. We recommend getting a wristband with your contact information to put on your child’s wrist so that in the event they get lost, we can contact you immediately. Anyone lost or missing someone should find a festival organiser or go to the welfare tent to seek help.

 

The only forms of identification accepted are:

 

Valid passport

Valid drivers licence

PASS identification card

You must have the original document, copies are not accepted.

faqs.question: Bus
faqs.answer:
The nearest bus stop is at Wych Cross (about 1.5 miles from Pippingford) and is serviced by:

 

261 East Grinstead to Uckfield.

 

270 East Grinstead to Brighton.

 

By special request drivers on the 261 East Grinstead to Uckfield route may stop outside the entrance to Pippingford on the A22.

 

All taxis should be pre booked.

faqs.question: Can I cook or BBQ?
faqs.answer:
Absolutely! Gas cookers are allowed in the main campsite up to a canister size of 3.9Kg. Larger canisters are not allowed into the campsite.

 

BBQs are only allowed inside the designated areas which will be clearly marked.
